Vice President Mike Pence visited Louisiana to discuss the state's response to the coronavirus pandemic. He expressed gratitude for the partnership between the federal government and the state, and praised Louisiana's efforts in slowing the spread of the virus. Pence emphasized the importance of reopening schools and stated that the government will provide testing, personal protective equipment, and other resources to support this. He also announced the deployment of testing resources to nursing homes across the country. Pence and other officials stressed the need for continued vigilance in following health guidelines, such as wearing masks and practicing good hygiene. They encouraged the people of Louisiana to work together to flatten the curve and protect the most vulnerable.